                        <title xml:lang="en">Commentary on Leviticus</title>
                        
                        
                        
                        <note>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Includes a commentary on the first pericope of Leviticus (chpater 1:1-5:26) of apparently Abu al-Faraj Furḳan.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>The fragment includes an Arabic translation of chapters 2:1-5:13.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Of the Hebrew text only the opening words are given.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Has scant masoretic notes.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Quotes several Karaite authorities.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </note>
                        
                        
                        
